e on, help me with this elevator.\'94 \'93You\'92re drunk,\'94 I said to him. \'93Come on, skip it and let us get upstairs.\'94 \'93So would you be drunk,\'94 said the white woolly jacket man. \'93So would you be drunk comrade old comrade. Listen, where\'92s Frank?\'94 \'93Where do you think he is?\'94 \'93In this fellow Henry\'92s room where the crap game is.\'94 \'93Come on with us,\'94 I said. \'93Don\'92t fool with those buttons. That\'92s why you stop it all the time.\'94 \'93I can fly anything,\'94 said the woolly jacket man. \'93And I can fly this old elevator. Want me to stunt it?\'94 \'93Skip it,\'94 Al said to him. \'93You\'92re drunk. We want to get to the crap game.\'94 \'93Who are you? I\'92ll hit you with a bottle full of champagne wine.\'94 \'93Try it,\'94 said Al. \'93I\'92d like to cool you, you rummy fake Santa Claus.\'94 \'93A rummy fake Santa Claus,\'94 said the bald man. \'93A rummy fake Santa Claus. And that\'92s the thanks of the Republic.\'94 We had gotten the elevator stopped at my floor and were walking down the hall. \'93Take some bottles,\'94 said the bald man. Then, \'93Do you know why I\'92m drunk?\'94 \'93No.\'94 \'93Well, I won\'92t tell you. But you\'92d be surprised. A rummy fake Santa Claus. Well well well. What are you in, comrade?\'94 \'93Tanks.\'94 \'93And you, comrade?\'94 \'93Making a picture.\'94 \'93And I\'92m a rummy fake Santa Claus. Well. Well. Well. I repeat. Well. Well. Well.\'94 \'93Go and drown in it,\'94 said Al. \'93You rummy fake Santa Claus.\'94 We were outside the room now. The man in the white woolly coat took hold of Al\'92s arm with his thumb and forefinger. \'93You amuse me, comrade,\'94 he said. \'93You truly amuse me.\'94 I opened the door. The room was full of smoke and the game looked just as when we had left it except the ham was all gone off the table and the whisky all gone out of the bottle. \'93It\'92s Baldy,\'94 said one of the crap shooters. \'93How do you do, comrades,\'94 said Baldy, bowing. \'93